Apologies for the mistake in the API base URL. The provided API domain is incorrect; it should be `api.enedis.fr` instead of `api.enode.com`. Please update the `ENODE_API_BASE_URL` in the `.env` file:
```javascript
ENODE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.enedis.fr/v1
```
Then, update the `enodeApi.js` file to use the correct base URL from the environment variables:
```javascript
// enodeApi.js
const axios = require('axios');
require('dotenv').config();

const fetchData = async (endpoint) => {
  const config = {
    baseURL: process.env.ENODE_API_BASE_URL,
    headers: {
      Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.ENODE_API_KEY}`,
    },
  };

  try {
    const response = await axios.get(endpoint, config);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching data:', error);
    throw error;
  }
};

module.exports = fetchData;
```
This should resolve the issue, and you should be able to run the script without any further errors.

